@node Kick3



	PCD Manager	version 2.2a				Aug-10-1996

	Allenbrand Brice - Ringard' Production.

	-> Kick 3.x required.


	Thumbnail builder with build-in selection.
	Written in C non-ANSI and Amiga system friendly, to have the smallest
	executable file.

	A graphic card enables PCD to use better graphics routines.
	CD32 + SX-1 as well.


	@{"Tooltypes" link Tooltypes}

	@{"Commands" link Cmds}

	@{"QuickStart" link KickSt}



	@{"More" link More}

	@{"Important" link about}

	@{"Changes" link Changes} Important !

	@{"Bugs" link bugs}

@endnode


@node Tooltypes


INPUT_DIR=CD0:			Default input directory.

OUTPUT_DIR=TMP:			Default output directory.

MAX_NB_DIA=100			Set the thumbnail screen for 100 pictures.


@endnode


@node cmds


Resolution :		from 192x256 upto 3072x2048

Transformation :	here you can select the way PCD handle the colors

			Normal			Hemm...normal
			Enhanced		better quality

	_The Enhanced color mode doesn't use more memory, but the quality
	 is better.

			B&W			Black & white

	_In BW mode, you only need 1/3 of memory amount required for the
	 color mode.

READ :			Read the given input directory and look for PCD files

START :			After selecting one or more pictures, handle them
			and write the resulting IFF24 to the given output
			directory.

QUIT :			Quit.

ALL/CLEAR/INVERT	Quick for selecting the pictures.



NEW in 2.2:

SAVE INDEX :		Save the thumbnail screen. Only possible when
			there are pictures on it.

Placing the pointer over a picture in the thumbnail screen, holding right
mouse button enable you to magnify it.


@endnode

@node KickSt



	Insert a PhotoCD in your favorite CD-Rom player.
	Run PCD
	Choose the input directory (CD0:....)
	Choose the output directory
	READ and wait....
	SELECT your lovely pictures with the mouse.
	select the resolution and the way PCD tranforms the colors.
	START and wait....
	QUIT PCD



@endnode

@node More



	_The conversion time depends on the memory amount of your Amiga.

	_The IFF saving routines can handle 3 different buffers depending
	 on your available memory. Off course ByteRunComp1 is used.

	_PCD2IFF24 & PCD Manager are only converters. They don't do much
	 more, because there exist enough image processing programs and
	 they will do it better.

	_PCD2IFF24 & PCD Manager can be used with VMM

@endnode

